sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant PayloadProc as payload-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant KServe as KServe Model Server<br/>HTTPS
    participant ExtProvider as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 1: User Inference Request (API Key)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-{key_id}_{secret}
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>(NetworkPolicy-protected, no auth)
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Query key hash (SHA-256)<br/>constant-time comparison
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key metadata + subscription
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Validation result
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>(resolve subscription tier)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription + rate limit info
    Note over Authorino: Inject X-MaaS-Username,<br/>X-MaaS-Group, X-MaaS-Subscription headers
    Note over Authorino: OPA: check group membership
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + identity headers
    Note over Gateway: Limitador enforces<br/>TokenRateLimitPolicy
    Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc: request body
    Note over PayloadProc: Extract model name from body<br/>Set X-Gateway-Model-Name header
    PayloadProc->>K8sAPI: Read ExternalModel CR + Secret
    K8sAPI-->>PayloadProc: Provider config + API key
    Note over PayloadProc: Resolve provider, translate API format,<br/>inject provider API key
    PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Transformed request
    Note over Gateway: Strip Authorization header<br/>(prevent credential exfiltration)

    alt Internal Model (KServe)
        Gateway->>KServe: Forward inference request<br/>(no auth header)
        KServe-->>Gateway: Prediction response
    else External Model (via ServiceEntry)
        Gateway->>ExtProvider: Forward to external provider<br/>(provider API key injected)
        ExtProvider-->>Gateway: Provider response
    end

    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response (OpenAI-compatible)

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 2: API Key Creation

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer K8s token
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation<br/>(K8s TokenReview, no API keys allowed)
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + X-MaaS-* headers
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>X-MaaS-Username, X-MaaS-Group headers
    MaaSAPI->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview (verify permissions)
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSAPI: SAR result
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Store key hash + metadata<br/>(per-key salt via key_id)
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Stored
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: API key (sk-oai-{key_id}_{secret})<br/>shown once only
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON: { api_key: "sk-oai-..." }

    Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 3: Tenant Reconciliation (Platform Deploy)

    Note over K8sAPI: Tenant CR created/updated
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: maas-controller watches Tenant CR
    Note over K8sAPI: Kustomize render from embedded overlays
    Note over K8sAPI: Post-render: inject AuthPolicies,<br/>TelemetryPolicies, DestinationRules
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply: Deployment, Service,<br/>ServiceAccount, NetworkPolicy, HTTPRoute,<br/>ClusterRole, CronJob, AuthPolicy, TRLP
